{"parse":{"title":"Gonfaloniere","pageid":20661446,"revid":860102819,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg/220px-Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"179\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg/330px-Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg/440px-Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"831\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Origine_della_Compagnia_della_Misericordia_in_Firenze.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The body of a dead woman is brought before the <a href=\"/wiki/Gonfaloniere_of_Justice\" title=\"Gonfaloniere of Justice\">Gonfaloniere of Justice</a>  in Florence in 1425, the legendary origin of the <i>Compagnia della Misericordia</i></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Gonfalonier</b> (in Italian: <i>Gonfaloniere</i>) was the holder of a highly prestigious <a href=\"/wiki/Medieval_commune\" title=\"Medieval commune\">communal</a> office in <a href=\"/wiki/Italy_in_the_Middle_Ages\" title=\"Italy in the Middle Ages\">medieval</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Italian_Renaissance\" title=\"Italian Renaissance\">Renaissance Italy</a>, notably in <a href=\"/wiki/Florence\" title=\"Florence\">Florence</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Papal_States\" title=\"Papal States\">Papal States</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The name derives from <i><a href=\"/wiki/Gonfalone\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gonfalone\">gonfalone</a></i> (in English, gonfalon), the term used for the banners of such communes.\n</p><p>In Florence, the office was known as <a href=\"/wiki/Gonfalonier_of_Justice\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gonfalonier of Justice\">Gonfalonier of Justice</a> (<i>Gonfaloniere di Giustizia</i>) and was held by one of the nine citizens selected by the drawing lots every two months, who formed the city's government, or <a href=\"/wiki/Signoria_of_Florence\" title=\"Signoria of Florence\">Signoria</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (August 2013)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> In the papal states, it was known as <a href=\"/wiki/Gonfalonier_of_the_Church\" title=\"Gonfalonier of the Church\">Gonfalonier of the Church</a> or Papal Gonfalonier.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BritannicaGonfalonier_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BritannicaGonfalonier-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Other central and northern Italian communes, from <a href=\"/wiki/Spoleto\" title=\"Spoleto\">Spoleto</a> to the <a href=\"/wiki/County_of_Savoy\" title=\"County of Savoy\">County of Savoy</a>, elected or appointed <i>gonfalonieri.</i>  The <a href=\"/wiki/House_of_Bentivoglio\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"House of Bentivoglio\">Bentivoglio family</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Bologna\" title=\"Bologna\">Bologna</a> aspired to this office during the sixteenth century.  However, by the year 1622, when <a href=\"/wiki/Artemisia_Gentileschi\" title=\"Artemisia Gentileschi\">Artemisia Gentileschi</a> painted a portrait of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pietro_Gentile&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Pietro Gentile (page does not exist)\">Pietro Gentile</a> as a gonfaloniere of <a href=\"/wiki/Bologna\" title=\"Bologna\">Bologna</a>, with the <i>gonfalone</i> in the background, the office had merely symbolic value.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Gonfaloniere&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Capitano_del_popolo\" title=\"Capitano del popolo\">Capitano del popolo</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Condottieri\" title=\"Condottieri\">Condottieri</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gonfalonier_of_the_Church\" title=\"Gonfalonier of the Church\">Gonfalonier of the Church</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Podest%C3%A0\" title=\"Podest\u00e0\">Podest\u00e0</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Gonfaloniere&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Viti, Paolo; Zaccaria, Raffaella Maria (1989). <i>Archivio delle Tratte: Introduzione e inventario</i>. Rome: Archivio di Stato di Firenze.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Archivio+delle+Tratte%3A+Introduzione+e+inventario&amp;rft.pub=Rome%3A+Archivio+di+Stato+di+Firenze&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.au=Viti%2C+Paolo&amp;rft.au=Zaccaria%2C+Raffaella+Maria&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGonfaloniere\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:no